title: Does what it says
comment: For the most part, it works great.  Thanks for your effort in getting Qt onto Android.  My only issue came when I had a Qt app that needed only a couple libs.  Ministro got the required libs and everything worked as expected.  Then months later, I had another Qt app that needed the same libs that were already on my device and some extra ones.  Ministro downloaded the missing libs, but those seemed to be somehow incompatible with the already existing libs on my device.  The Qt program crashed when it tried to use the mixture of old and new Qt libraries.   When I deleted all the Qt libs from my phone and let Ministro get them all again, the app magically worked.  Ministro needs to be smarter about mixing libraries together.
